{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17602692","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17602692"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:30:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:30:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15702"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15702","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15702"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.41,0.16,0.3,0,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8393"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67270"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8393","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8393"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15702"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52722"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4467"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8503"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20223"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20224"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22519"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67270"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EEndometritis is inflammation of the endometrial lining of the uterus.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most common cause of acute endometritis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pelvic inflammatory disease","Postpartum infection","Retained products of conception","Termination of pregnancy","Uterine instrumentation"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAcute endometritis most commonly occurs due to \u003Cstrong\u003Eretained products of conception\u003C/strong\u003E following pregnancy events such as miscarriage or delivery. While \u003Cstrong\u003Etermination of pregnancy\u003C/strong\u003E can lead to endometritis, it is less common with modern sterile techniques. \u003Cstrong\u003EPelvic inflammatory disease\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes a more widespread infection of the upper genital tract. \u003Cstrong\u003EUterine instrumentation\u003C/strong\u003E during procedures like hysteroscopy carries a small risk of endometritis. \u003Cstrong\u003EPostpartum infection\u003C/strong\u003E can cause endometritis but is less common with prophylactic antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe retained tissue provides a medium for bacterial growth, leading to inflammation of the endometrium. Common organisms include mixed aerobic and anaerobic bacteria from the vaginal flora. Symptoms typically include pelvic pain, fever, and abnormal vaginal discharge.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute endometritis most commonly occurs following pregnancy-related events, particularly retained products of conception.","Endometritis is inflammation of the endometrium that can be acute or chronic."],"references":["Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Singh N, Sethi A. Endometritis - Diagnosis,Treatment and its impact on fertility - A Scoping Review. JBRA Assist Reprod. 2022 Aug 4;26(3):538-546. doi: 10.5935/1518-0557.20220015. PMID: 35621273; PMCID: PMC9355436.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"i